@node "why" "WHY!?!"

    Yes that's true, we already have billions of Icons but now we have 
    @{" CED Icons! " SYStEM "CED.guide/Sound CED.guide/RimShot q"} Well, it all started when i was looking after a good icon
    to Iconian but I couldn't find one so I made my own, and after a while I
    made some more icons and I could just not stop and... well you know the
    rest...

    Ced icons is @{b}CARDWARE@{ub} so if you like it and use some of my icons, brushes 
    etc. you'll have to send @{" ME " LINK "contact"} a funny postcard.
    This is NOT the last time you'll see this text about the CARDWARE stuff...
@endnode
@node icons "Icons"

    Well, I thought it was time for me to make a contribution to the MagicWB
    package.
 
    I have made a whole new Prefs-template because the old one is so ugley.
    I don't know if you will like mine better but I love it!!!
    
    In the Prefs-drawer you will find some Prefs-icons (Strange...) with
    MY new template. Use them!!!

    If some of you think that my icons are pretty much alike those from Martin
    Huttenloher or Roman Patzner etc. your're probably right cause many of the
    icons in this package are nothing more than repainted MagicWB icons so if
    you find some of your icons in this package a bit modified you should be
    happy cause that means that it's great!!!
                                                                             
    Ced icons is @{b}CARDWARE@{ub} so if you like it and use some of my icons, brushes 
    etc. you'll have to send @{" ME " LINK "contact"} a funny postcard.
    
    Well there ain't much more to say you'll se what they are for.
@endnode
@node TM-B "TM-Brushes"

    They are all anim-brushes and that's the biggest change that I have made.
    I know that anim-brushes need a bit more memory but they are looking far
    better than a single brush. 
    
    The ones in the 'MWBDock-Brushes' drawer is the same as you get with 
    MagicWB 2.o, BUT mine are Animbrushes!!!
    The icons in the 'Other_Brushes' drawer is just some other brushes... 
    
    Well... Check them out!!! 
@endnode
@node © "Copyright stuffs"

@{b}COPYRIGHT STUFFS@{ub}
                                                                   
    MagicWB is Copyright ©1992-1994 by Martin Huttenloher.
                                                                         
    This package is @{b}CARDWARE.@{ub}
    So if you like it and use some of my icons, brushes etc. you'll have to
    send me a funny postcard.
    
    There is NO Copyright at this Icon collection but there is still some 
    things that I would like you to consider:    
                                                                     
    You may modify the icons for personal or public use so long as you 
    acknowledge my name in your credits AND you MUST send me a copy!
    (I want to see what you've done with them =-))
                                                                         
    You may not use the icons, or the imagery of them, unchanged or not, on 
    any other platfrom besides Amiga. If you do that, I'll kill you.
                                                                         
    These icons may be freely distributed via BBSs, InterNet/UseNet, software 
    libraries such as Aminet CD-ROM, and magazines as long as the archive is 
    not modified in any way!!! 
                                                                         
    I will NOT be held responsible for any damage caused by using the icons 
    contained within this archive. You, the user, take full responsibility by 
    using these icons.
    (But I can't see how some icons might damage your system!)
                                                                     
@{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}
                                                                           
    As I told you this package is @{b}CARDWARE@{ub} so if you like them and use some
    of my icons, brushes etc. you'll have to send @{" ME " LINK "contact"} a funny postcard.
    Or even better, send me a large amount of $...   

    Even if you feel the icons are not worth any donation, I'd still love
    to hear from you because its good to know who (and how many) are using
    them! I want to hear what you think of them - whether they're good,
    bad or totally suck! (Hope not :-))
@endnode
